-Dropdown options
    Selenium support: <select></select>
        Structure: <select>, <option value=index>, content/text

    Step 1: Xac dinh select locator & element
    Step 2: Goi class Select tu method support ui
    Step 3: Su dung strategy to find select
        - 1. Select by visible text
        - 2. Select by index
        - 3. Select by value

- Customize Select class
    Create a class extend parent class
    Create a constructor follow parent
    Create a method(s)

- iFrame
    - How:
        Step 1: Locate iFrame element.
        Step 2: switch to iFrame
        Step 3: Locate desired element and interact with it
        Step 4: switch back to parent frame
    - Exception: no such element: Unable to locate element (do co 1 html document nam trong parent html document)


- Mouse hover
    Step 1: dung Action class tu Selenium
    Step 2: locate elements by narrow down searching technique
    Step 3: goi methods actions.moveToElement(elem).perform()

- Narrow down searching
    C1: multiple matching
        How: Create a List then loop over this list, access to each index to call the element
        Disadvantage: difficulty to maintenance
    C2: Tim list cua parent element
        Check null
        Loop over parent element from element (use element.findElement() |NOT driver.findElement())
        Define an Action object
        Mouse over/ loop over each element

- JavaScript Alert
    - Expectation: get content, click button, input field
    - Usage: khong dung driver.findElement, ma su dung wait
    - Step 1: Tao object WebElement, Alert, WebDriverWait
    - Step 2: find Element locator
    - Step 3: Click on Element
    - Step 4: Use wait